node.text: it’s safe to say this years recap video is different than that of 2019. (You can look at my very small list of 3 IGTV videos to see that). It’s been one of the hardest years for the entire world & so much hardship, uncertainty, and fear that has followed. Waking up and watching the news literally began to feel like a different universe because in no way would I have believed what this year would entail if you told me exactly a year ago today as I was writing up my caption for my 2019 recap. My disappointments and hard times of this year feel like nothing compared to what so many have gone through this year. But every person was affected in some way and each individuals feelings are valid. In reality what did I lose? Travel? Experiences? Maybe. But what did I gain? New perspective. A new mindset. New things to be grateful for. My mental health in 2019 was at a low. There was days I literally couldn’t leave my house because I was so consumed with anxiety and fear. I didn’t even know of what at times but it was just always there. My main accomplishment of this year was how I prioritized my mental health and got it back to the place I needed it to be at. Yes this was a hard year but being with my family and focusing on the little things really got me through it. Being under the same roof as your family, living in the same space for months on end without leaving your house but more than a handful of times can really teach you a thing or two about those around you. I am so grateful for my friends and family because this year taught me that it’s not about where you are or what you’re doing but who your with and the energy created. I know as we enter into 2021 there is still so much uncertainty but I know there’s still knowledge to be uncovered and hope. I hope to continue to prioritize my mental health and keep those around me safe and healthy. I’m grateful for another year doing what I love and this is just a short recap of some of the moments I captured. I love you all and happy new year. Stay safe and count your blessings💗

node.text:
what a year. For the last month I’ve been complaining about how rough 2019 was on me mentally but looking at all these clips made me smile and appreciate the good times. i am blessed with a beautiful life, family, job, friends, and so much more. I am looking forward to the goals I have in 2020 and the first step to that is to leave 2019 on a good note. I’m going to appreciate the good, bad, mistakes, chances to grow, and even the things about myself I hate most! I want to learn to be more of a listener and to stop holding myself back from things based on fear or what people will think. I have so many changes coming in 2020 but I’m ready! Thank you 2019 for this amazing year, I’ll look back and be grateful for all that happened cause it’s made me more mature and helped me grow into who I am. I lost some people I thought would be in my life forever, learned to appreciate the meaning behind quality over quantity, learned to be less selfish, became more empathetic, got an apartment , travelled to 6 new countries, worked with dream brands, signed with a new agency, and became closer with my family than ever before. I would say a pretty good year. 
To 2020🥂

node.text:
GIVEAWAY!!!

Here’s how my first Zoom call with the BBxEllie product testers went! Loved getting feedback about the products we’re creating together and I want to invite 6 more of you for the next round of samples! Participants will receive the final product they gave feedback on - for free!

How To Enter
♡ Tag a friend who you know loves a good lip plumper
♡ Follow @beaubble
♡ Comment on my latest Beaubble post (link in bio and/or stories)

[*No purchase necessary. US residents only. Contest ends 9/19 at 11:59PM PST. Must be 18 years or older to win. By entering, you acknowledge that this giveaway is in no way sponsored, endorsed by or associated with Instagram. Winners will be notified directly.]

#BBxEllie #19andahalf #beaubble
